  "title": "Achieving Quality Chemical Measurements in Foods",
  "abstract": "Quality measurement is the core of modern analytical chemistry and analytical services such as in food analysis.This chapter highlights the importance of quality assurance concepts in IS0/IEC17025 and discusses the infrastructure and development of metrology in chemistry (MiC) concerning reliable measurement in food analysis. MiC is a discipline concerning accurate chemical measurements through the implementation of traceability, comparability and measurement uncertainty (MU). Proficiency testing (PT) programmes using assigned reference values for melamine in milk and pesticides in green tea are used as case studies to illustrate the actual difficulties in the determination of trace levels of organic contaminants in food matrices by food testing laboratories. Standardization of laboratory quality assurance protocols and application of MiC are considered to be vital to ensure reliable analytical results in food measurement.",
